            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1507752476505-q14--am-i-entitled-to-access-to-students--academic-records-for-any-reason-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#8cd51512-5cf4-40c2-89ab-4d65f1b8cd77" href="#accordion-content-1507752476505-q14--am-i-entitled-to-access-to-students--academic-records-for-any-reason-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1507752476505-q14--am-i-entitled-to-access-to-students--academic-records-for-any-reason-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Q14: Am I entitled to access to students’ academic records for any reason?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1507752476505-q14--am-i-entitled-to-access-to-students--academic-records-for-any-reason-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1507752476505-q14--am-i-entitled-to-access-to-students--academic-records-for-any-reason-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1507752476505 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="502e4696-7dd6-41c8-9636-6568a8b5a1fc" >

    <p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In general, you do not have the right to consult a student’s academic record. Faculty who serve on appeals panels or who are charged with academic advising may confidentially access these records for that purpose only. Chairs/Directors and their specified administrative staff may access records for administrative purposes only and are not authorized to share that record with faculty. If you have questions regarding whether you may access an academic record for a particular purpose speak to the Associate Registrar, Enrollment Services.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#502e4696-7dd6-41c8-9636-6568a8b5a1fc");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1507752477247-q15--what-should-i-do-with-unclaimed-students--work-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#8cd51512-5cf4-40c2-89ab-4d65f1b8cd77" href="#accordion-content-1507752477247-q15--what-should-i-do-with-unclaimed-students--work-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1507752477247-q15--what-should-i-do-with-unclaimed-students--work-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Q15: What should I do with unclaimed students’ work?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1507752477247-q15--what-should-i-do-with-unclaimed-students--work-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1507752477247-q15--what-should-i-do-with-unclaimed-students--work-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1507752477247 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="5ff0540d-20f9-435b-802b-baa512109b4f" >

    <p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Course Management Policy states that students’ work must be returned to them confidentially. Putting student work in a box outside your office is not permitted.&nbsp; Departments/Schools are required to develop policies on the confidential disposal of work.&nbsp; Under FIPPA you must retain all unclaimed student work, including final exams, for one year from the date received.&nbsp; Student grades and evaluation comments should be kept confidential.&nbsp; It is advisable not to put the mark and comments on the front page of the document.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#5ff0540d-20f9-435b-802b-baa512109b4f");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1507752478600-q16--can-i-have-students-working-in-groups-hand-in-one-assignment-together-with-their-names-and-their-ryerson-student-identification-numbers-on-the-first-page-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#8cd51512-5cf4-40c2-89ab-4d65f1b8cd77" href="#accordion-content-1507752478600-q16--can-i-have-students-working-in-groups-hand-in-one-assignment-together-with-their-names-and-their-ryerson-student-identification-numbers-on-the-first-page-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1507752478600-q16--can-i-have-students-working-in-groups-hand-in-one-assignment-together-with-their-names-and-their-ryerson-student-identification-numbers-on-the-first-page-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Q16: Can I have students working in groups hand in one assignment together with their names and their Ryerson Student Identification Numbers on the first page?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1507752478600-q16--can-i-have-students-working-in-groups-hand-in-one-assignment-together-with-their-names-and-their-ryerson-student-identification-numbers-on-the-first-page-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1507752478600-q16--can-i-have-students-working-in-groups-hand-in-one-assignment-together-with-their-names-and-their-ryerson-student-identification-numbers-on-the-first-page-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1507752478600 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="127b32d6-5940-454d-bb65-c082a42172a2" >

    <p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The concern is that name plus student ID number permits someone else with enough information to impersonate another student.&nbsp; The more information disclosed, the better able some one would be in committing fraud.&nbsp; A similar approach to that outlined in the Course Management Policy Section 2.2(f) should be followed where only part of the student number is included. It is recommended that the last 4 digits be used.&nbsp; In other words, professors can request that students working on group assignments hand in projects listing a portion of the student ID number and no names.&nbsp; In this way the other students in the group will not be privy to the entire student ID number.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#127b32d6-5940-454d-bb65-c082a42172a2");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1507752479350-q17--how-can-i-now-take-students--attendance-at-weekly-classes-and-final-exams--what-if-the-student-doesn-t-have-their-onecard-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#8cd51512-5cf4-40c2-89ab-4d65f1b8cd77" href="#accordion-content-1507752479350-q17--how-can-i-now-take-students--attendance-at-weekly-classes-and-final-exams--what-if-the-student-doesn-t-have-their-onecard-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1507752479350-q17--how-can-i-now-take-students--attendance-at-weekly-classes-and-final-exams--what-if-the-student-doesn-t-have-their-onecard-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Q17: How can I now take students’ attendance at weekly classes and final exams? What if the student doesn’t have their OneCard?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1507752479350-q17--how-can-i-now-take-students--attendance-at-weekly-classes-and-final-exams--what-if-the-student-doesn-t-have-their-onecard-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1507752479350-q17--how-can-i-now-take-students--attendance-at-weekly-classes-and-final-exams--what-if-the-student-doesn-t-have-their-onecard-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1507752479350 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="52fe8cfe-6a24-4eb3-8807-83ff7ad097f3" >

    <p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Attendance at lectures, seminars and labs can still be taken, but professors should be sensitive to how this information is gathered. The student’s full name and complete student ID number should not be circulated.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>For final exams, invigilators should walk around the room to verify student photo ID cards on a student-by-student basis, noting the attendance on a sheet of names and numbers, and students should sign their individual exams.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
<p>According to the&nbsp;<a href="/senate/policies/pol135.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>Senate’s Examination Policy 135<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span></a>, Section III (B)(5) students must present relevant photo identification; the policy does not specify that only the OneCard will suffice.&nbsp; There is no need to take a student’s photograph at an exam.&nbsp; It is the student’s responsibility to ensure that he/she brings proper identification.&nbsp; If a student does not have any photo ID, the instructor should first try to confirm that the student is in the class, and the student should be required to bring identification with a signature to the instructor’s office as soon as possible after the exam.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#52fe8cfe-6a24-4eb3-8807-83ff7ad097f3");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1507752480952-q18--what-can-an-instructor-do-upon-becoming-aware-that-a-student-is-taking-photos-or-video-of-the-lecture--other-students--or-discussion-period--is-this-a-violation-of-student-privacy--what-about-the-instructors--privacy-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#8cd51512-5cf4-40c2-89ab-4d65f1b8cd77" href="#accordion-content-1507752480952-q18--what-can-an-instructor-do-upon-becoming-aware-that-a-student-is-taking-photos-or-video-of-the-lecture--other-students--or-discussion-period--is-this-a-violation-of-student-privacy--what-about-the-instructors--privacy-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1507752480952-q18--what-can-an-instructor-do-upon-becoming-aware-that-a-student-is-taking-photos-or-video-of-the-lecture--other-students--or-discussion-period--is-this-a-violation-of-student-privacy--what-about-the-instructors--privacy-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Q18: What can an instructor do upon becoming aware that a student is taking photos or video of the lecture, other students, or discussion period? Is this a violation of student privacy? What about the instructors’ privacy?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1507752480952-q18--what-can-an-instructor-do-upon-becoming-aware-that-a-student-is-taking-photos-or-video-of-the-lecture--other-students--or-discussion-period--is-this-a-violation-of-student-privacy--what-about-the-instructors--privacy-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1507752480952-q18--what-can-an-instructor-do-upon-becoming-aware-that-a-student-is-taking-photos-or-video-of-the-lecture--other-students--or-discussion-period--is-this-a-violation-of-student-privacy--what-about-the-instructors--privacy-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1507752480952 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="e883b3be-2189-4da5-9889-27ead0a53c38" >

    <p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Students’ answers, student images – these are the personal information of students.&nbsp; The actual lecture is the teaching material of the instructor and is not meant to be publicly available without his/her consent; teaching materials are protected against disclosure from a formal access request under FIPPA.&nbsp; The image of the instructor is his/her personal information therefore both the instructor’s lecture and image would require the instructor’s consent for capture.</p> 
<p>If notice about the intent to capture the lecture by audio or visual recording is provided in advance to the instructor and students, no one’s privacy would be violated.&nbsp; Students with concerns could approach the instructor in advance.&nbsp; If the request to record the lecture stems from an Access Centre request, then these concerns would be relayed to the Access Centre.&nbsp; Ryerson is obliged under the Ontario Human Rights Code and the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (Bill 118) to seek a reasonable accommodation so that students with disabilities are not at a learning disadvantage because of their special needs.&nbsp; Please contact the Access Centre for further information (ext. 5290).&nbsp; See also the Senate policy&nbsp;<a href="/senate/policies/pol159.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>Academic Accomodation of Students with Disabilities 159<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span></a></p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#e883b3be-2189-4da5-9889-27ead0a53c38");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
