                            Q22: How is my research impacted by FIPPA?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1507752571481-q22--how-is-my-research-impacted-by-fippa-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1507752571481-q22--how-is-my-research-impacted-by-fippa-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1507752571481 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="033a8886-f755-4dff-ae34-c0ce39b35248" >

    <p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Research and teaching materials are excluded from FIPPA.&nbsp; Thus, if someone were to make an FOI request for your research notes on a project, the University would advise the requestor that those records are not subject to FIPPA. However, FIPPA specifies that the subject matter and the amount of funding for research (but not the source of funding) is information that must be made available if requested. For more information consult with OVPRI.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#033a8886-f755-4dff-ae34-c0ce39b35248");});</script></div>

